    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. but i've been reading some stuff online saying that originalism is basically just a way for conservative judges to push their own agenda under the guise of 'textualism'. how do scholars respond to the criticism that it's more about politics than actual law?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
